For {= facility_or_operation =}+ public recycling facilities, processor sites, transfer/material-recovery facilities, or other source-identified operating recycling sites in the Greater Toronto Area, cover each of the {= evidence_facet =} evidence facets listed below by supplying a public source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per facet) that establishes the submitted site's public operating identity, material stream, handling capability, authority, or scale provenance. A facility or operation is a company/operator paired with a named facility, public site, or tightly scoped local operating site; this should be specific enough to separate sibling sites while allowing ordinary aliases for the same site. Passive collection points, retail take-back storefronts, textile/donation bins, and list-only depot hosts are not themselves in-scope operations unless the cited page establishes that the submitted site is an actual recycling, recovery, transfer, MRF, processing, or comparable material-handling operation.

The useful signal is public-source provenance over recycling operations, not a lead list, price sheet, export-target map, procurement recommendation, contact-enrichment file, residential-address inference, or confidence/date/source-class bookkeeping exercise.

Evidence facets:
- `regional_operating_role`: a GTA site/operator operating role, such as MRF, recycler, recovery facility, transfer/processing site, paper recycler, plastic reprocessor, converter, or comparable public recycling operation. A store, bin, public drop-off host, or collection-list row does not satisfy this facet merely by receiving items.
- `accepted_material_streams`: material streams source-stated as handled, accepted for handling, processed, transferred, sorted, recycled, or otherwise managed by the submitted facility/operation, such as OCC, mixed paper, fibre, HDPE, LDPE film, PP, PET, rigid plastics, regrind, rolls, blue-box material, plastics, paper, or comparable material streams. A generic list of items accepted across many depots or retail drop-off points is not enough without a site-specific operating tie for that material stream.
- `processing_capability`: sorting, baling, grinding, shredding, washing, drying, pelletizing, compounding, densifying, transfer/processing, MRF operation, or comparable handling/processing capability at the submitted site. Simple receipt, public drop-off, bin hosting, retail take-back, or forwarding to an unnamed processor is not a processing capability.
- `public_authority_or_scale_signal`: public permit, registry, site-specific municipal/producer-responsibility/contract/routing, trade-public announcement, official capacity, throughput, tonnage, plant size, permitted activity, or comparable public authority/scale signal tied to the submitted facility/operation.

The submitted facility or operation ought to be a real recycling, recovery, transfer, MRF, paper-recycling, plastic-reprocessing, converting, processing, or comparable public material-handling operation tied to the Greater Toronto Area. Sources should be public, accessible, and page-evaluable; snippets alone do not count. A pure scrap broker, exporter, quote marketplace, commodity-stocklot listing, equipment seller, generic corporate sustainability page, generic resident recycling education page, contact page, price/RFQ page, procurement guide, broad market/trend page, retail store locator, public collection depot list, textile-bin list, or producer take-back drop-off list does not count merely by mentioning recyclable materials, accepted items, or addresses. Public business/facility addresses are in scope only when a public source states them; residential inference is outside scope.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the submitted company/operator and facility, public site, named location, or tightly scoped local operating site. A row in a crowded locator/list page is insufficient unless that row or the page section establishes facility-specific operating and material-handling evidence for the submitted item.
- The page must source-state a GTA municipality, public facility/site address, named GTA facility, named local operating site, site-specific municipal/producer-responsibility routing, contract, permit, or other clear GTA operating tie.
- The page must visibly earn the evidence role for the submitted facet through page content, source ownership, document context, or a focused facility/operator entry. A generic company-wide material or capability page works only when that page itself ties the claim to the submitted GTA facility/site/operation. A broad directory/listing, education page, depot locator, retail store locator, collection-bin list, producer drop-off list, RFQ, marketplace, export/import, stocklot, broker, price, contact, or equipment-catalog page does not work unless it independently establishes focused public facility/material/capability provenance for the submitted item.
- The page must state a concrete finding matching the submitted evidence facet: for `regional_operating_role`, a GTA operating role for the submitted site/operator; for `accepted_material_streams`, material streams handled, accepted for handling, processed, transferred, sorted, recycled, or otherwise managed by the submitted facility/operation; for `processing_capability`, a concrete handling or processing capability beyond passive receipt/drop-off/bin hosting; for `public_authority_or_scale_signal`, a public footprint, permit/registry, site-specific municipal/producer-responsibility/contract/routing, trade-public, capacity, throughput, tonnage, plant-size, permitted-activity, or comparable scale/authority signal.
- A single municipal, producer-responsibility, retail, or directory list page should not be copied across many sibling depots, stores, bins, or host sites. It can support a local tie or authority only when the submitted item is otherwise a real in-scope operating facility and the page gives site-specific evidence; it cannot by itself satisfy accepted-material or processing-capability facets for many passive collection locations.
